{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 16:54:32.220566", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope and Topology\n- Fabric: Multi-tier Clos with EBGP everywhere. Super-spine AS 65000; spines and leaves use EBGP. Inter-router links are 172.16.0.0/16 /31s. Each leaf advertises a distinct host subnet 10.<pod>.<leaf>.0/24.\n- Devices: super_spine_router_0; spines: spine_router_0_0, spine_router_0_1; leaves: leaf_router_0_0 (leaf-00), leaf_router_0_1 (leaf-01); hosts: pc_0_0 (should be 10.0.0.0/24), pc_0_1 (should be 10.0.1.0/24).\n\nFindings\n\n1) Host configurations (edge L3)\n- pc_0_0:\n  - IP 10.0.0.2/24, default via 10.0.0.1 (expected for leaf-00).\n- pc_0_1:\n  - IP 10.0.0.2/24, default via 10.0.0.1.\n  - This is incorrect. pc_0_1 is attached to leaf-01 which serves 10.0.1.0/24 (gateway 10.0.1.1). pc_0_1 should be on 10.0.1.0/24, not 10.0.0.0/24. It is also duplicating the same IP (10.0.0.2) as pc_0_0 (on a different L2 segment).\n\n2) Reachability tests (data plane symptoms)\n- pc_0_0 -> 10.0.1.2 (intended pc_0_1 address) fails with “From 172.16.0.35 Destination Host Unreachable”.\n  - 172.16.0.35 is leaf_router_0_1’s upstream address, indicating the leaf cannot deliver to 10.0.1.2.\n- pc_0_0 -> 10.0.1.1 (leaf-01 gateway) succeeds with low RTT.\n  - Confirms fabric path to leaf-01 is healthy.\n- pc_0_0 <-> pc_0_1 pings to 10.0.0.2 show immediate replies with ~0.06 ms RTT.\n  - Both hosts have 10.0.0.2 configured, so these are self-pings (they are pinging their own local IP on each host), not inter-host connectivity.\n\n3) Leaf ARP state (last-hop delivery)\n- leaf_router_0_1: “10.0.1.2 dev eth4 INCOMPLETE”\n  - The leaf cannot resolve the MAC for 10.0.1.2 on its host-facing interface, consistent with the host not being on 10.0.1.0/24.\n- leaf_router_0_0: ARP entry present for 10.0.0.2 on its host-facing interface.\n  - Confirms pc_0_0 is correctly attached and reachable at L2/L3.\n\n4) Control plane (BGP) health\n- All BGP adjacencies across leaves, spines, and super-spine are Established and exchanging prefixes:\n  - leaf_router_0_0 and leaf_router_0_1 each have 4 established EBGP peers; PfxRcd matches expectations.\n  - Spines have 6 established peers; super-spine has 8 established peers.\n- Routing tables:\n  - leaf_router_0_0: connected 10.0.0.0/24; receives 10.0.1.0/24 and all other leaf subnets via BGP.\n  - leaf_router_0_1: connected 10.0.1.0/24; receives 10.0.0.0/24 and others via BGP.\n  - Spines and super-spine show expected BGP-learned routes for both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 pointing to the appropriate leaves.\n- No signs of BGP flaps, missing prefixes, or asymmetric anomalies.\n\nAssessment\n\nA) Anomalies detected\n- Host IP misconfiguration on pc_0_1:\n  - Wrong IP/subnet: pc_0_1 is set to 10.0.0.2/24 with default gw 10.0.0.1 instead of 10.0.1.2/24 with gw 10.0.1.1.\n  - Duplicate IP: pc_0_1 and pc_0_0 both use 10.0.0.2, albeit on different L2 segments.\n- Resulting symptoms:\n  - leaf_router_0_1 ARP for 10.0.1.2 remains INCOMPLETE; it cannot deliver frames to the intended host address in its directly connected subnet.\n  - Traffic destined to 10.0.1.2 from elsewhere fails with ICMP Host Unreachable sourced by leaf_router_0_1’s upstream address.\n  - pc_0_1’s default route points to an unreachable gateway (10.0.0.1 is not on pc_0_1’s connected L2), so pc_0_1 is effectively isolated except for local self-traffic.\n\nB) Localized faulty device\n- Fault localized to host pc_0_1 configuration (edge host), not the fabric or routing devices.\n\nC) Root cause\n- Incorrect L3 configuration on pc_0_1:\n  - Interface IP and default gateway belong to the wrong subnet for its attachment. Expected: 10.0.1.2/24 via 10.0.1.1 on leaf_router_0_1; observed: 10.0.0.2/24 via 10.0.0.1.\n\nNetwork health summary\n- Fabric control plane (EBGP across leaves, spines, super-spine) is healthy and converged; all expected leaf networks are distributed across the fabric.\n- Data plane within the fabric is functional (e.g., pc_0_0 to 10.0.1.1 works). Last-hop delivery to pc_0_1 fails due to the host’s incorrect IP/gateway, not due to fabric issues.\n\nEvidence highlights\n- pc_0_1 ip/route: 10.0.0.2/24, default via 10.0.0.1.\n- leaf_router_0_1 ip addr: 10.0.1.1/24 on host-facing interface (eth4).\n- leaf_router_0_1 ip neigh: 10.0.1.2 INCOMPLETE.\n- pc_0_0 -> 10.0.1.2: “From 172.16.0.35 Destination Host Unreachable.”\n- BGP summaries on all routers: Established neighbors with expected prefix counts; RIBs contain both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 with correct next-hops.\n\nConclusion\n- The data center fabric and routing are operating normally.\n- The only identified fault is a host-side misconfiguration on pc_0_1 (incorrect IP/subnet and gateway), leading to unreachable 10.0.1.2 and ARP failures at leaf_router_0_1.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 13334, "output_tokens": 4591, "total_tokens": 17925, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 11264}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 3008}}}
